-- Egypt Cassation Court Suspends Work Over Mursi Decree, MENA Says
-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y
-- 2012-11-28T12:36:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-28/egypt-cassation-court-suspends-work-over-mursi-decree-mena-says.html
Egypt’s Court of Cassation, the
final appeals court, will suspend operations until the
revocation of President Mohamed Mursi’s decree granting himself
additional powers, state-run Middle East  News Agency  reported.  Many judges and prosecutors have suspended work in protest
over a decision they say undercuts their legitimacy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salma El Wardany in Cairo at 
 selwardany@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  